  "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\n\r\nIf `KeyStore.BlockAuthorAccount` is set but it's privkey is not found Nethermind just logs\r\n\r\n```\r\nnethermind_1  | 2022-06-11 17:05:38.6616|A private key for address: 0x88dfc82cf71fdeb23f82c33a202f6e2d19ac0541 does not exists in directory /nethermind/configs/keystores. \r\nnethermind_1  | 2022-06-11 17:05:38.6616|Not able to unlock the key for 0x88dFc82CF71fdeb23f82C33a202f6E2D19AC0541 \r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is bad UX because it's not obvious on first sight that there's anything wrong. The log above in buried into many other init logs. When it's time for you to seal blocks nothing will happen.\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\n\r\nThe process should exit 1 immediately.\r\n",
